I just attempted the bonus puzzle, and if you're not a NY baseball fan, it's essentially impossible. They say it's "Monday/ Tuesday" difficult, but I have several Naticks that I have to run the alphabet on. And since there are six (!) empty squares, it's going to be a slog. 
Here's my list:
A baseball players name (18A), crossing both the name of an author of a baseball story in a book of basebal stories, neither of which work I've ever heard of (3D), and a kids clothing brand I have no clue about (14D);

The name of somebody that somebody famous dubbed "Mr. Baseball" (27A), crossing both that clothing brand again (14D), and random letters in a New York district (23D);

Name of a [USA only?] insurance company (42D), crossing the name of a novel by an author that I've at least heard of, but have never read (47A).

Yeah, yeah. Learning opportunity, blah, blah, blah. But I just don't care about the game enough to think it's worth learning this kind of trivia.

